Sentencas: In the present investigation Samarium doped barium cerate electrolyte powder of (1-x)Ce(0.2)Sm0(.2)O(2-delta) - xBaCe(0.8)Sm(0.2)O(3-delta) (where x = 0.1 mol fraction) stoichiometry formula is successfully synthesized through wet chemical route.
Titulo: Thermal, structural and electrical properties of samarium doped barium cerate electrolyte for SOFCs

Sentencas: A SDC-BCS nanocomposite electrolyte is premeditated with respect to its thermal, structural, morphological properties and conductivity performance.
Titulo: Thermal, structural and electrical properties of samarium doped barium cerate electrolyte for SOFCs

Sentencas: The crystal structure and microstructure of the SDC-BCS composite is investigated from XRD and SEM analysis.
Titulo: Thermal, structural and electrical properties of samarium doped barium cerate electrolyte for SOFCs

Sentencas: TG analysis reveals that the calcination temperature (900 degrees C) of the as prepared powder sample.
Titulo: Thermal, structural and electrical properties of samarium doped barium cerate electrolyte for SOFCs

Sentencas: The crystal structure of as prepared SDC-BCS composite powder is identified as cubic perovskite with orthorhombic distortions occurred at 900 degrees C. From TEM analysis, the particle size is found to be around 32 nm.
Titulo: Thermal, structural and electrical properties of samarium doped barium cerate electrolyte for SOFCs

Sentencas: SEM analysis reveals that the existence of dual phase microstructure in the composite at 1400 degrees C.
Titulo: Thermal, structural and electrical properties of samarium doped barium cerate electrolyte for SOFCs

Sentencas: The preparation of dense SDC-BCS nanocomposite with the development of dual phase microstructure is achieved for the better ionic conductivity in SDC-BCS nanocomposites for SOFC application.
Titulo: Thermal, structural and electrical properties of samarium doped barium cerate electrolyte for SOFCs
